                         Systems Acquisition Office

newsboy.gif (4096 bytes)

                                         The SAO Procurement Office has issued a
                                   Fisheries Research Vessel Request for Information!

                               [blueline.gif]

   The Systems Acquisition Office (SAO) was established in 1991 as the
   primary program development and acquisition office under the National
   Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration. SAO's programs range from
   atmospheric surveillance to fleet modernization and from systems
   development to systems deployment.

   SAO Acquisitions
   ASOS
   Automated Surface Observing System (ASOS)
   Thumbnail display of an AWIPS Product.
   Advanced Weather Interactive Processing System (AWIPS)
   GOES Satellite
   Geostationary Operational Environmental Satellite (GOES)
   Gulfstream IV Plane and the RONALD H. BROWN
   Marine and Air Platform Acquisition Office (MAPAO) NEXRAD Tower
   Next Generation Weather Radar (NEXRAD) Polar Satellite
   Polar Operational Environmental Satellite (POLAR)

